# Testing Rules for sfxClanker

When testing sfxClanker:
- Run pytest on tests/ to verify utils functionality.
- Run mypy . to check type hints.
- Mock external dependencies (requests, pydub) in tests.
- Ensure query tests match exact design strings.
- For audio tests, mock pydub.AudioSegment.
- Run tests before and after changes.
- Use pytest -v for verbose output.
- Aim for 80%+ coverage on utils.

Testing goals: prevent regressions, ensure modularity works.

# Git Rules for Testing
- Before testing: git status, git pull origin main
- After testing: git add ., git commit -m "Test: description", git push origin main
